LICENSE - DECISION NEEDED
==========================

This file is a placeholder, not a real license yet.

Since this project is work product created during a BITS Pilani PS-1
internship for Instruworks LLC FZ (a private company), the right license
- if any - depends on facts this file can't assume:

1. Does Instruworks want this code to remain fully proprietary (no public
   license at all - the default under copyright law if no license is
   granted)?
2. Does BITS Pilani's PS-1 program have any IP-ownership terms that apply
   to work produced during the internship?
3. Is there any intention to open-source this project later, and if so,
   under what terms (MIT, Apache 2.0, GPL, etc. all have different
   implications for who can use/modify/resell the code)?

Adding a permissive open-source license (e.g. MIT) here without answering
those questions first could give away rights Instruworks may want to keep.

Recommended next step: ask your supervisor (Eng. Charkha) directly whether
Instruworks wants a specific license here, or whether the repo should
simply remain unlicensed/proprietary (i.e. delete this file and rely on
default copyright protection, which is often the right choice for
internal business tools that were never intended for public release).
